common gecko
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an attractively marked gecko commonly found in the north of the South Island and in the east of the North Island from Wellington to Coromandel.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:Environment
Region:[none]
See:brown gecko
Pronunciation:
Notes: <i>Hoplodactylus maculatus,</i> aka Matua gecko
